feminism, and geomantic criticism. The book presents a compelling and timely "green" perspective through which to understand key works of Asian American literature and leads the field of ecocriticism into neglected terrain"--cProvided by publisher.  a16 0aAmerican literaturexAsian American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aEnvironmental protection in literature. 0aEcology in literature. 0aEcocriticism.1 aFitzsimmons, Lorna,d1957-eeditor.1 aChae, Youngsuk,eeditor.1 aAdams, Bella,eeditor. 0aRoutledge interdisciplinary perspectives on literature ;v35.  aPS 153 A84 A74 2015c1hUAAU-Bi0162035232279  aPS 153 A84 A74 2015wLCc1i0162035232279lON_SHELFmUAAUGp$150.00rYsYtBOOKu2/4/201501ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2005085394bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/71652586